com.camerontec.catalys.server.ha.collections.synchronization

Class SynchronizationAttemptIntervalCalculator

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.camerontec.catalys.server.ha.collections.synchronization.SynchronizationAttemptIntervalCalculator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IProcessingReplayResponsesListener

    public class SynchronizationAttemptIntervalCalculator
extends Object
implements IProcessingReplayResponsesListener
    Class which calculates the interval when next periodic synchronization attempt should be tried when passive site replication is configured.

    Calculation is done in synchronized state, after synchronization is completed.

    The interval of synchronization attempts is self-adjust as follows:

    - if there was no data returned in synchronization attempt, we wait for some time, T1 (synchronizationAttemptIntervalInitial), to do the next attempt.

    - if the same thing happens more than N times, we wait for 2 * T1 instead etc. until we reach the maximum waiting time, T2 (synchronizationAttemptIntervalMax).
